Reasoning: The paper discusses the challenges and requirements of communication and localization technologies for unmanned vehicles in industrial automation applications, which falls under the scope of robotics (cs.RO) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also considers the use cases and specific requirements of unmanned vehicles in Industry 4.0, which involves systems and control (cs.SY) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the need for more flexible communication technologies, which could fall under software engineering (cs.SE).
